Package edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.fitting

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ObjectiveFunction
    Describes a function that returns a (real) scalar and takes a vector of parameters.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BisquareLinearFit  
    BisquareLinearFit.WlsObjectiveFunction
    A class implementing weighted sum of squares on a linear model.
    CentroidImageObject
    An image object of arbitrary shape whose position is determined by the (intensity-weighted) centroid over its region in a mask.
    DifferentialEvolutionMinimizer
    This class implements the differential evolution algorithm for function minimization.
    FitParameters
    A class that holds the parameters that are the result of a fit of an ImageObject.
    GaussianFitter3D
    Performs a three-dimensional gaussian fit to an object in an image using a maximum likelihood method assuming Poisson distributed pixel intensities (once converted to units of photons).
    GaussianFitter3DWithCovariance
    Performs a three-dimensional gaussian fit to an object in an image using a maximum likelihood method assuming Poisson distributed pixel intensities (once converted to units of photons).
    GaussianImageObject
    An ImageObject that fits to a three-dimensional gaussian that is symmetric in x-y and has no covariance between any of the dimensions.
    GaussianImageObjectWithCovariance
    An ImageObject that fits to a three-dimensional Gaussian.
    ImageObject
    An object in an image with some spatial extent that can be fit to some function.
    NelderMeadMinimizer
    A function minimizer that implements the Nelder-Mead or Downhill Simplex method.
